decks.notes: The concept of this deck is to utilize the aggressive strategy of Aragorn, King of Gondor, to quickly overwhelm the opponent in a Duel Commander 1 vs 1 format. The deck includes a mix of efficient creatures, removal spells, counterspells, and disruptive creatures to control the battlefield while also putting pressure on the opponent. With a focus on tempo and efficiency, the deck aims to maintain board presence and disrupt the opponent's game plan, while also having the ability to close out the game swiftly with powerful creatures like True-Name Nemesis and Mantis Rider. By combining aggression with control elements, this deck aims to outpace and outmaneuver the opponent to secure victory.

The deck focuses on building a strong defensive board while utilizing various auras and equipment to increase the commander's power and protect it from removal spells. It includes a mix of protection spells, card draw engines, and utility creatures to help control the game and ensure the commander can stay on the battlefield. The goal is to create a resilient and evasive threat that can quickly close out the game with potent combat damage. The deck also includes a suite of disruption and removal spells to disrupt opponent's strategies and keep the board clear. The key strategy is to protect and enhance the commander to establish a dominant position on the battlefield and secure victory.
